```
Then extract VCs from the SMT file, run Z3 to get models, and use the name map + ast mapping to decode.

The file to verify is at: /Users/mchiesa/work/projects/2026-02-dafny-liftings/LeetcodeDafny/leetcode_tests/0/code-dafny-with-spec.dfy

IMPORTANT: First copy the file to /Users/mchiesa/work/projects/2026-02-dafny-liftings/experiment/p0_approachB.dfy and work on that copy. Do not modify the original.

Here is the code:
```dafny
predicate twoSumPost(nums: seq<int>, target: int, result: seq<int>)
  reads {}
{
  |result| == 2
  && 0 <= result[0] < |nums|
  && 0 <= result[1] < |nums|
  && result[0] != result[1]
  && nums[result[0]] + nums[result[1]] == target
}

method twoSum(nums: seq<int>, target: int) returns (result: seq<int>)
  requires |nums| >= 2
  requires exists i, j :: 0 <= i < |nums| && 0 <= j < |nums| && i != j && nums[i] + nums[j] == target
  ensures  twoSumPost(nums, target, result)
{
    var hashTable := map[];
    var i := 0;

    while i < |nums|
    {
        var complement := target - nums[i];
        if complement in hashTable
        {
            return [hashTable[complement], i];
        }
        if nums[i] !in hashTable{
            hashTable := hashTable[nums[i] := i];
        }
        i := i + 1;
    }

    return [];
}
```

The postcondition requires that the returned result has 2 elements pointing to distinct indices whose values sum to target. The precondition guarantees such a pair exists.

Strategy: Start by running Dafny verify to see errors. If stuck, use the SMT tools to extract the VC, get spurious models from Z3, decode them using the name map, and understand what Z3 is missing. Use that information to craft better invariants.

Work iteratively: add invariants, run verify, read errors, if stuck use SMT analysis. Report your final result: VERIFIED or FAILED (with what errors remain).

